TextChange: Survival is often about acquiting possessions which could be considered being materialistic. Many survivalist shows are about how people gather and store items to help them survive. Having more clothes, more food, more comforts, will help anyone survive longer in any situation than others who do not. The more things that someone collects, the more situations they will be able to overcome. Therefore, in a sense, being materialistic could lead to better survival rates. Someone who does not worry about collecting things and acquiring possessions may encounter situations that they are not prepared for.
